elements.description:
`api-headers-editor`
An element to render headers edior based on AMF data model.

By default it renders headers form. The user has an option to switch to
source editing mode. `code-mirror` element is used in the later case.

## AMF data model

This element renders pre-configured form of headers based on
[AMF's](https://github.com/mulesoft/amf) json/ld data model.
From the model select `http://raml.org/vocabularies/http#header`
node which contains list of headers defined for current object
(it can be method, trait, security scheme etc).
The model is resolved to internal data model by `api-view-model-transformer`
element.

If the element is used without AMF model `allowCustom` property must be
set or otherwise user won't be able to add new header to the editor.

### Example

```html
<api-headers-editor id="editor" allow-disable-params></api-headers-editor>
<script>
let data = await getAmfModel();
editor.amfModel = data;
data = data[0]['http://raml.org/vocabularies/document#encodes'][0];
data = data['http://raml.org/vocabularies/http#endpoint'][0];
data = data['http://www.w3.org/ns/hydra/core#supportedOperation'][0];
data = data['http://www.w3.org/ns/hydra/core#expects'][0];
data = data['http://raml.org/vocabularies/http#header'];
(first endpoint, first method, headers array)
editor.amfHeaders = data;
editor.addEventListener('value-changed', (e) => console.log(e.detail.value));
< /script>
```

### Example without AMF

```html
<api-headers-editor id="editor" allow-disable-params allow-custom></api-headers-editor>
<script>
editor.addEventListener('value-changed', (e) => console.log(e.detail.value));
< /script>
```

## Setting value when model is set

Model values has priority over value set on the editor.
If `amfModel` is set and value has been altered programatically there
are two possible outcomes:

1) If `allowDisableParams` is set, model values are automatically
disabled if model item is not in the value
2) If `allowDisableParams` is not set, model values are always
added to generated values. Or rather new value is added to the existing
model as custom values.

properties.name: isPayload
properties.description:
Set to true when the request can carry a payload.
It's required for calculating headers errors.

properties.name: eventsTarget
properties.description:
Events handlers target. By default the element listens on
`window` object. If set, all events listeners will be attached to this
object instead of `window`.

properties.name: _oldEventsTarget
properties.description: An event target used to attach listeners.

properties.name: model
properties.description: View model to use to render the form.

properties.name: optionalOpened
properties.description: Set to true to show optional parameters (not required by the API).

properties.name: hasOptional
properties.description:
Computed value from `allowHideOptional` and view model.
`true` if current model has any optional property.

properties.name: allowHideOptional
properties.description:
If set it computes `hasOptional` property and shows checkbox in the
form to show / hide optional properties.

properties.name: renderOptionalCheckbox
properties.description: Computed flag to determine if optional checkbox can be rendered

properties.name: allowDisableParams
properties.description:
If set, enable / disable param checkbox is rendered next to each
form item.

properties.name: allowCustom
properties.description:
When set, renders "add custom" item button.
If the element is to be used withouth AMF model this should always
be enabled. Otherwise users won't be able to add a parameter.

properties.name: narrow
properties.description: Renders items in "narrow" view

properties.name: renderEmptyMessage
properties.description:
Computed value. The form renders empty message (if supported by
the form element). It occurs when model is not set and allowCustom
is not set

properties.name: amfModel
properties.description:
Generated AMF json/ld model form the API spec.
The element assumes the object of the first array item to be a
type of `"http://raml.org/vocabularies/document#Document`
on AMF vocabulary.

properties.name: ns
properties.description: A namespace for AMF model

properties.name: currentPanel
properties.description: Reference to currently rendered headers editor.

properties.name: aware
properties.description: `raml-aware` scope property to use.

properties.name: amfHeaders
properties.description: List of headers defined in AMF model to render.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Headers value.

properties.name: viewModel
properties.description:
Generated view model fore the headers from `amfModel`.
This is automatically set when `amfModel` is set.

properties.name: contentType
properties.description:
Value of a Content-Type header.
When this value change then editor update the value for the content type. However,
to change a single header value, please, use `request-headers-changed` event with `name`
and `value` properties set on the detail object.

properties.name: sourceMode
properties.description: When set to true then the source edit mode is enabled

properties.name: _transformerTarget
properties.description: Events target for tranformer

properties.name: _contentTypeRe
properties.description: Regexp to search for content type value

properties.name: noDocs
properties.description:
Prohibits rendering of the documentation (the icon and the
description).
Note, Set is separately for `api-view-model-transformer`
component as this only affects "custom" items.

properties.name: readonly
properties.description: When set the editor is in read only mode.

properties.name: autoValidate
properties.description:
Automatically validates headers agains AMF model when value change.
Note, it only works with form editor.

methods.name: filterHeaders
methods.description:
Filter array of headers and return not duplicated array of the same headers.
Duplicated headers should be appended to already found one using coma separator.

params.name: headers
params.description:
Headers array to filter. All objects in headers array must have "name"
               and "value" keys.

methods.name: headersToString
methods.description: Parse headers array to Raw HTTP headers string.

params.name: headersArray
params.description:
List of objects with "name" and "value"
properties.

return.desc: A HTTP representation of the headers.

methods.name: headerItemToString
methods.description:
Transforms a header model item to a string.
Array values are supported.

methods.name: headersToJSON
methods.description:
Parse HTTP headers input from string to array of objects containing `name` and `value`
properties.

params.name: headers
params.description: Raw HTTP headers input or Headers object

return.desc:
The array of objects where properties are `name` as a header
name and `value` as a header content.

methods.name: _headersStringToJSON
methods.description:
Parse headers string to array of objects.
See `#toJSON` for more info.

methods.name: _hedersToJSON
methods.description:
Parse Headers object to array of objects.
See `#toJSON` for more info.

methods.name: _oldCombine
methods.description:
Helper method for old system: combine headers list with encoding value.
Note that this function will update the original array.

params.name: encoding
params.description: An encoding string from the old request.

return.desc: True if encoding has been added to the array.

methods.name: getContentType
methods.description: Get the Content-Type value from the headers.

params.name: headers
params.description: Either HTTP headers string or list of headers.

return.desc: A content-type header value or null if not found

methods.name: replaceHeaderValue
methods.description: Replace value for given header in the headers list.

params.name: headers
params.description:
A headers object. Can be string, array of objects or
Headers object.

methods.name: getHeaderError
methods.description: Get error message for given header string.

return.desc: An error message or null if the headers are valid.

methods.name: _eventsTargetChanged
methods.description:
Removes old handlers (if any) and attaches listeners on new event
event target.

params.name: eventsTarget
params.description:
Event target to set handlers on. If not set it
will set handlers on the `window` object.

methods.name: computeFormRowClass
methods.description: Computes class name for each form item depending on the item state.

params.name: optionalOpened
params.description: True if optional parameters are rendered.

methods.name: toggleOptionalParams
methods.description: Toggles visibility of optional parameters.

methods.name: _getForm
methods.description:
Returns a reference to the form element, if the DOM is ready.
This only works with `iron-form` that is in the DOM.

return.desc:
Iron form element. It may be `undefined` if local
DOM is not yet initialized.

methods.name: _getValidity
methods.description: attribute automatically, which should be used for styling.

methods.name: serializeForm
methods.description: Link to the form's serialize function.

return.desc:
Serialized form values or `undefined` if DOM is not ready.
Note, `undefined` is returned **only** if DOM is not yet ready.

methods.name: _computeHasOptionalParameters
methods.description:
Computes if any of the parameters are required.
It iterates over the model to find any first element that has `required`
propeerty set to `false`.

params.name: allowHideOptional
params.description:
State of `allowHideOptional` property.
If `false` this function always returns `false`.

params.name: record
params.description:
Change record. Note, it does not checks for
optional parameters each time the model changes. It rescans the model
when splices changed.

return.desc: `true` if model has at leas one alement that is not required.

methods.name: _computeRenderCheckbox
methods.description: Computes value for `renderOptionalCheckbox` property.

methods.name: _computeIsCustom
methods.description:
Computes if given model item is a custom property (not generated by
AMF model transformation).

return.desc:
`true` if `isCustom` property is set on model's schema
property.

methods.name: addCustom
methods.description:
Adds empty custom property to the list.

It dispatches `api-property-model-build` custom event that is handled by
`api-view-model-transformer` to build model item.
This assumem that the transformer element is already in the DOM.

After the transformation the element pushes or sets the data to the
`model`.

params.name: opts
params.description:
Additional options:
- inputLabel {String} - Forces a label of the input

methods.name: _removeCustom
methods.description:
Removes custom item from the UI.
This can only be called from `dom-repeat` element so it contain's
`model` property.

methods.name: computeIsOptional
methods.description:
Computes if model item is optional.
The items is always optional if is not required and when `hasOptional`
is set to `true`.

return.desc: `true` if the model item is optional in the form.

methods.name: _computeRenderEmptyMessage
methods.description: Computes value for `renderEmptyMessage`.

params.name: allowCustom
params.description: True if the form allows to add custom values.

return.desc: `true` when allowCustom is falsy set and model is empty

methods.name: _getAmfKey
methods.description: Returns compact model key for given value.

return.desc:
Compact model property name or the same value if
value not found in the context.

methods.name: _ensureAmfModel
methods.description: Ensures that the model is AMF object.

methods.name: _ensureArray
methods.description:
Ensures that the value is an array.
It returns undefined when there's no value.
It returns the same array if the value is already an array.
It returns new array of the item is not an array.

methods.name: _getValue
methods.description: Gets a signle scalar value from a model.

params.name: model
params.description: Amf model to extract the value from.

params.name: key
params.description: Model key to search for the value

methods.name: _getValueArray
methods.description: Gets values from a model as an array of `@value` properties.

params.name: model
params.description: Amf model to extract the value from.

params.name: key
params.description: Model key to search for the value

methods.name: _hasType
methods.description: Checks if a model has a type.

return.desc: True if model has a type.

methods.name: _hasProperty
methods.description: Checks if a shape has a property.

methods.name: _computePropertyArray
methods.description: Computes array value of a property in a model (shape).

methods.name: _computePropertyObject
methods.description:
Computes a value of a property in a model (shape).
It takes first value of a property, if exists.

methods.name: _computeHasStringValue
methods.description: Tests if a passed argumet exists.

methods.name: _computeHasArrayValue
methods.description:
Computes if passed argument is an array and has a value.
It does not check for type or value of the array items.

methods.name: _computeDescription
methods.description: Computes description for a shape.

methods.name: _computeServerVariables
methods.description: Computes value for `serverVariables` property.

methods.name: _computeEndpointVariables
methods.description: Computes value for `endpointVariables` property.

methods.name: _computePayload
methods.description: Computes value for the `payload` property

methods.name: _computeReturns
methods.description: Computes value for `returns` property

methods.name: _computeSecurity
methods.description: Computes value for `security` property

methods.name: _computeHasCustomProperties
methods.description: Computes value for `hasCustomProperties` property.

methods.name: _computeApiVersion
methods.description: Computes API version from the AMF model.

methods.name: _computeEncodes
methods.description: Computes model's `encodes` property.

methods.name: _computeDeclares
methods.description: Computes list of declarations in the AMF api model.

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeReferences
methods.description: Computes list of references in the AMF api model.

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeWebApi
methods.description: Computes AMF's `http://schema.org/WebAPI` model

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeServer
methods.description: Computes value for `server` property that is later used with other computations.

methods.name: _computeEndpointUri
methods.description: Computes endpoint's URI based on `amfModel` and `endpoint` models.

methods.name: _getBaseUri
methods.description:
Computes base URI value from either `baseUri`, `iron-meta` with
`ApiBaseUri` key or `amfModel` value (in this order).

return.desc: Base uri value. Can be empty string.

methods.name: _getAmfBaseUri
methods.description: Computes base URI from AMF model.

params.name: protocols
params.description:
Listy of supporte dprotocols. If not
provided and required to compute the url it uses `amfModel` to compute
protocols

methods.name: _ensureUrlScheme
methods.description:
A function that makes sure that the URL has a scheme definition.
If no supported protocols information is available it assumes `http`.

params.name: protocols
params.description:
List of supported by the API protocols
An array of string like: `['HTTP', 'HTTPS']`. It lowercase the value.
If not set it tries to read supported protocols value from `amfModel`
property.

methods.name: _computeProtocols
methods.description: Computes supported protocols by the API.

methods.name: _computeExpects
methods.description: Computes value for the `expects` property.

methods.name: _computePropertyValue
methods.description:
Tries to find an example value (whether it's default value or from an
example) to put it into snippet's values.

methods.name: _computeEndpoints
methods.description: Computes list of endpoints from a WebApi model.

return.desc: Always returns an array of endpoints.

methods.name: _computeEndpointModel
methods.description: Computes model for an endpoint documentation.

methods.name: _computeEndpointByPath
methods.description: Computes model for an endpoint documentation using it's path.

methods.name: _computeMethodModel
methods.description: Computes method for the method documentation.

methods.name: _computeOperations
methods.description: Computes list of operations in an endpoint

methods.name: _computeMethodEndpoint
methods.description: Computes an endpoint for a method.

methods.name: __computeMethodsListForMethod
methods.description:
Computes a list of methods for an endpoint that contains a method with
given id.

return.desc: A list of sibling methods or undefined.

methods.name: _computeType
methods.description: Computes a type documentation model.

methods.name: _computeReferenceType
methods.description: Computes a type model from a reference (library for example).

params.name: reference
params.description: AMF model for a reference to extract the data from

return.desc: Type definition or undefined if not found.

methods.name: _computeSecurityModel
methods.description: Computes model for selected security definition.

methods.name: _computeDocument
methods.description: Computes a documentation model.

methods.name: _resolve
methods.description: Resolves a reference to an external fragment.

methods.name: _getExampleValue
methods.description: Gets string value for an example data model.

params.name: isJson
params.description:
If set it checks if the `raw` value is valid JSON.
If it isn't then it parses structured value.

methods.name: _computeExampleFromStructuredValue
methods.description: Computes an example from example structured value.

return.desc: Javascript object or array with structured value.

methods.name: _computeStructuredExampleValue
methods.description: Computes value with propert data type for a structured example.

methods.name: _sourceModeChanged
methods.description:
Handler for `sourceMode` change.

Opens desired editr.

methods.name: _readonlyChanged
methods.description: Sets current value of `readonly` on the source editor.

methods.name: _editorValueChanged
methods.description: Updates the value when current editor's value change.

methods.name: modelToValue
methods.description: Creates a headers string from a model.

params.name: model
params.description:
Optional, model to process. If not set it uses
`this.viewModel`

methods.name: _cmKeysHandler
methods.description:
Code mirror's ctrl+space key handler.
Opens headers fill support.

methods.name: _modelFromValue
methods.description:
Called when switching from source view to form view.
Updates view model with values defined in text editor.

Only headers existing in `value` are going to be present in the model.
Otherwise headers will be disabled.

It does nothing if `value` or `viewModel` is not defined.

methods.name: _findModelIndex
methods.description: Finds item position in model by name.

return.desc: Items position or `-1` if not found.

methods.name: createCustom
methods.description: Creates a custom header model item.

methods.name: _headersChangedHandler
methods.description:
Handler tor the `request-headers-changed` event.
Updates the editor value to the value of the event detail object.

methods.name: _headerChangedHandler
methods.description:
Handler for the `request-header-changed` event.
It updates value for a single header.

methods.name: _contentTypeChangedHandler
methods.description:
Handler for `content-type-changed` event.
Uppdates it's value if from external source.

methods.name: _headerDeletedHandler
methods.description:
Handler for `request-header-deleted` custom event.
Deletes header from the editor.

methods.name: _detectContentType
methods.description: Detects and sets content type value from changed headers value.

methods.name: _valueChanged
methods.description:
Called by CodeMirror editor.
When something change n the headers list, detect content type header.

methods.name: _setValues
methods.description: Updates `value` when new value is computed by the editor.

methods.name: _copyToClipboard
methods.description: Coppies current response text value to clipboard.

methods.name: refresh
methods.description: Refreshes the CodeMirror editor when in `sourceMode`.
